description: From the present participle of Latin imminēre (“to overhang”), from mineō ("to project, overhang"), related to minae (English menace) and mons (English mount). Compare with eminent.

adjectives.description: imminent (comparative more imminent, superlative most imminent)

entries.meaning: about to happen, occur, or take place very soon, especially of something which won't last long.
